<div id="banner">
  <h1>Small Caps Test</h1>
</div>
<div class="content">
<p>Here's what it should look like:</p>
<img src="smallCaps-pic" />
<p>Here's what it does look like:</p>
<p style='font-size: 14pt; font-family: "Big Caslon"; margin-left: 12px'>
<span style="font-variant: small-caps;">Real Small Caps</span><br />
<span style="font-size: 11pt;"><span class="c">F</span>AKE <span class="c">S</span>MALL <span class="c">C</span>APS</span>
</p>

<p>(Real Small Caps use the small capitals glyphs from the font, which are usually sharper and differently-proportioned.)</p>

<h2>Results</h2>
<p>
Safari v64 capitalizes nothing.<br />
Safari v62 capitalizes everything.<br />
Safari v60 capitalizes nothing.<br />
OmniWeb 4.1 capitalizes nothing.<br />
Chimera 2002-02-12 uses Fake.<br />
IE 5.1 uses Fake.
</p>
